DURBAN- A 30-YEAR-OLD man is fighting for his life in a Durban hospital after he was shot in the head by an unknown gunman while he sat with friends outside a property in Morningside on Saturday night. Provincial police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said it was alleged that the victim was sitting outside a Percy Osborne Road property, drinking beers with his friend, when a suspect approached. “The suspect confronted the victim and pulled out a firearm and shot the victim in his head,” she said. Mbele said an ambulance was summoned. Emer-G-Med paramedics spokesperson Kyle van Reenen said paramedics were called to assist dRK Tactical security company on the scene just before 10pm on Saturday. “Reports are that the man sustained a single gunshot wound to the head and was found in a critical condition. He was treated and stabilised on scene before being taken to a nearby hospital under the care of an Emergency Care practitioner,” said van Reenen. Police said the motive for the incident is unknown at this stage. Mbele said no cartridges were found on the scene. “The witness that was found on the scene could not provide any details as he was heavily under the influence of liquor,” she said. Police said the suspect's identity is unknown. THE MERCURY